      "title": "",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 11
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## CP Data Structures\n\nMonitors the lifecycle and contention of **FencedLock**, **ISemaphore**, **IAtomicLong**, and **CP Sessions**.\n\nUnlike CPMap, these structures use **CP sessions** to guarantee safety: a client that acquires a lock or semaphore permit holds a session, and the server will auto-release the resource if the session expires (due to client crash or GC pause). Monitoring sessions alongside contention metrics is essential for detecting hung clients.\n\n**Data structure \u2192 CP group assignment in this cluster:**\n| Structure | Instances | CP Group |\n|-----------|-----------|----------|\n| FencedLock | lock0\u2013lock2 | group2 |\n| ISemaphore | sem0\u2013sem1 | group3 |\n| ISemaphore | sem2 | group7 |\n| IAtomicLong | counter0\u2013counter2 | group4 |\n| IAtomicLong | counter3\u2013counter4 | group6 |\n\n**Key questions this dashboard answers:**\n- Is any lock under high contention (high acquisition rate, or threads waiting for a permit)? *(Lock section)*\n- Are semaphore permits being exhausted \u2014 causing callers to block or time out? *(Semaphore section)*\n- Are atomic counters incrementing at the expected rate? *(AtomicLong section)*\n- Are any CP sessions at risk of expiring \u2014 indicating a hung or slow client? *(Sessions section)*\n\n**Note:** Lock wait time, CAS failure rate, and session count metrics are not yet exported by Management Center. The panels for those metrics will show \"No data\" until a future MC version exposes them."
      },
      "transparent": true
    },
